track_notes: A route using the Pennine Way.

Park off the A6024 just by the Derbyshire / Yorkshire boarder. Cross stile. There is a path of sorts running parallel with the clough, but you are sure to encounter plenty of mud (or snow in winter). Across Heyden Head bear for trig point.

Total time (including ops): 1h 50m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
